965
00:54:24,447 --> 00:54:26,607
I'm fine, thank you.

966
00:54:26,608 --> 00:54:28,807
- Pen, you're squashing my head!
- Ssh, ssh!

967
00:54:28,808 --> 00:54:30,915
I'm sorry, darling.

968
00:54:39,726 --> 00:54:42,766
- Ssh, ssh, ssh!
- I've got you. I'm here.

969
00:54:42,767 --> 00:54:45,565
Well done, Jerry.

970
00:54:45,567 --> 00:54:47,358
Right.

971
00:54:47,446 --> 00:54:50,285
- Have you got the gun?
- No, sorry, Richard.

972
00:54:50,285 --> 00:54:52,725
I put my foot down. I just
decided it was too dangerous.

973
00:54:52,726 --> 00:54:54,965
- Quite right.
- I simply don't trust myself around it.

974
00:54:54,965 --> 00:54:57,405
But I made sandwiches, egg mayo.
Anyone hungry?

975
00:54:57,406 --> 00:54:59,884
- Oh, great, I'm starving.
- Pen, I think we should get on.

976
00:54:59,885 --> 00:55:01,764
Yeah, come on, this way.

977
00:55:01,764 --> 00:55:03,709
Stay close to me, Jerry.

978
00:55:30,843 --> 00:55:32,443
You look fine in that hat.

979
00:55:32,444 --> 00:55:34,723
Mr and Mrs Chambord, from Qatar.

980
00:55:34,724 --> 00:55:36,042
<i>- Bonsoir.
- Bonsoir.</i>

981
00:55:36,043 --> 00:55:38,391
Mr Chabert, from Bordeaux.

982
00:55:39,082 --> 00:55:42,315
Mr and Mrs Ossman, from Hanoi.

983
00:55:42,323 --> 00:55:44,402
- Congratulations.
- <i>Merci.</i>

984
00:55:44,403 --> 00:55:46,202
Thanks for coming.

985
00:55:46,203 --> 00:55:50,322
Mr and Mrs Hicks and Mr and Mrs
Baxter from Houston, Texas.

986
00:55:50,323 --> 00:55:52,482
- Ah, that's us!
- Hey! <i>Bonsoir.</i>

987
00:55:52,482 --> 00:55:54,922
- So glad you made it. Long way to come.
- Howdy partner!

988
00:55:54,923 --> 00:55:57,922
- Real great to be here.
- We'll find time to talk later. Welcome.

989
00:55:57,923 --> 00:56:00,121
Of course, this is not
really a wedding.

990
00:56:00,122 --> 00:56:02,201
- It's a chance to do some business.
- Sweetheart.

991
00:56:02,202 --> 00:56:05,201
Well, you're not to bore us with all that
oil talk. I'm here to have some fun.

992
00:56:05,202 --> 00:56:08,761
Oh, we like fun, don't we?
Come along, missy.

993
00:56:08,762 --> 00:56:11,829
Thank you. It's a
mighty fine château.

994
00:56:12,682 --> 00:56:15,226
Mr and Mrs Beltrami, from Rome.

995
00:56:19,602 --> 00:56:23,433
- I think that went quite well.
- For now.

996
00:56:23,641 --> 00:56:26,000
Let's blend in.

997
00:56:26,001 --> 00:56:29,399
Darling, I need to powder my nose. Would
you be so kind as to accompany me?

998
00:56:29,400 --> 00:56:31,440
- It would be my pleasure.
- Thank you.

999
00:56:31,441 --> 00:56:33,320
- Ey-up.
- Jerry!

1000
00:56:33,321 --> 00:56:37,399
Merci. Well, Kate said
to blend in, didn't she?

1001
00:56:37,400 --> 00:56:40,032
- Here's to us.
- Yeah.

1002
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:46,879
- Which floor?
- Second floor.

1003
00:56:46,880 --> 00:56:48,672
Right.

1004
00:56:50,119 --> 00:56:51,911
Right.

1005
00:56:54,199 --> 00:56:56,308
Back in a tick.

1006
00:57:22,317 --> 00:57:28,103
That's it, that's her room.
OK, Jerry. 30 seconds.

1007
00:57:29,196 --> 00:57:31,917
Howdy, partner! How ya doin' there?

1008
00:57:31,918 --> 00:57:34,955
- Come on.
- I'm looking for the old John Wayne.

1009
00:57:34,956 --> 00:57:40,516
The, er... pissoir, the,
er... bog crapper? Any idea?

1010
00:57:40,517 --> 00:57:43,268
Sorry, sir, downstairs.
This floor is private.

1011
00:57:48,756 --> 00:57:51,636
Her window's open and there's
a ledge running to it.

1012
00:57:51,637 --> 00:57:53,194
A ledge? Ledge?

1013
00:57:53,195 --> 00:57:56,263
More like a balcony. Hold those.

1014
00:58:09,276 --> 00:58:11,699
- Slow, slow, slow.
- I am going slow.

1015
00:58:13,075 --> 00:58:15,433
- Don't look down.
- I'm not bloody looking down.

1016
00:58:15,434 --> 00:58:17,782
Oh... Oh!

1017
00:58:19,395 --> 00:58:20,914
Turn around, turn around.

1018
00:58:20,914 --> 00:58:25,754
See? Turn around. There you go.
That's it. You're all right now.

1019
00:58:25,755 --> 00:58:29,106
This is good. I got it.

1020
00:58:31,114 --> 00:58:32,832
Well done. Well done.

1021
00:58:32,833 --> 00:58:36,545
You're being very brave.
You're being very, very brave.

1022
00:58:37,353 --> 00:58:39,461
- Oh!
- Oh!

1023
00:58:40,353 --> 00:58:41,873
Oh, fuck!

1024
00:58:41,874 --> 00:58:43,032
Wait, wait, wait.

1025
00:58:43,033 --> 00:58:45,381
I've got you. I've got you.

1026
00:58:47,273 --> 00:58:50,822
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1027
00:59:06,071 --> 00:59:09,063
- Cats.
- And flowers.

1028
00:59:24,192 --> 00:59:26,703
The 19th century.

1029
00:59:28,311 --> 00:59:31,029
I'm gonna get changed.

1030
00:59:31,030 --> 00:59:32,735
<i>Excusez-moi.</i>

1031
00:59:35,951 --> 00:59:38,014
Go with her.

1032
01:00:07,350 --> 01:00:08,660
Ssh...

1033
01:00:20,108 --> 01:00:21,826
I'm coming.

1034
01:00:23,747 --> 01:00:26,979
Come in! <i>Entrez!</i>

1035
01:00:46,467 --> 01:00:48,186
What?

1036
01:00:48,187 --> 01:00:50,624
- You want to watch me get dressed now?
- Eh?

1037
01:00:50,626 --> 01:00:52,897
Get out! Get out!

1038
01:01:02,425 --> 01:01:05,089
She just... OK.

1039
01:01:09,145 --> 01:01:10,848
Ssh!

1040
01:01:12,985 --> 01:01:16,024
Oh, sorry. You're probably
wondering what I am doing.

1041
01:01:16,024 --> 01:01:19,105
- It's not...
- I'm so glad you're here.

1042
01:01:19,106 --> 01:01:20,383
Oh, there, there.

1043
01:01:20,384 --> 01:01:25,263
Now, just sit down and tell Auntie...
Miriam all your worries.

1044
01:01:25,264 --> 01:01:26,824
What's the matter?

1045
01:01:26,825 --> 01:01:29,863
I've made a terrible mistake.

1046
01:01:29,864 --> 01:01:33,464
He does not love me.
He never has and he never will.

1047
01:01:33,465 --> 01:01:36,023
I've sold myself to the devil.

1048
01:01:36,023 --> 01:01:40,103
- I'm a whore. I'm a devil's whore.
- No, no, you're not.

1049
01:01:40,104 --> 01:01:42,983
- No, no, no.
- Yes, yes, yes.

1050
01:01:42,984 --> 01:01:45,342
No, no, no, you're not.
Of course you're not.

1051
01:01:45,343 --> 01:01:50,422
Yes, I am. I'm a terrible,
horrible, shallow person.

1052
01:01:50,423 --> 01:01:52,941
I am a fake. I am a fake.

1053
01:01:52,942 --> 01:01:56,262
I am a fake. I am a fake.

1054
01:01:56,263 --> 01:01:57,701
No, don't say that about yourself.

1055
01:01:57,702 --> 01:02:03,142
From what I can tell, you're a highly original,
slightly highly strung, bright, imaginative girl.

1056
01:02:03,143 --> 01:02:04,541
- Really?
- Yes.

1057
01:02:04,541 --> 01:02:06,901
- You really think so?
- I do. I do. Really.

1058
01:02:06,902 --> 01:02:10,022
That is the nicest thing
anyone has ever said to me.

1059
01:02:10,023 --> 01:02:14,140
Oh, no! Oh, thank you.
Thank you, you're so nice.

1060
01:02:14,141 --> 01:02:15,890
No, I'm not, really.

1061
01:02:21,181 --> 01:02:25,061
Please excuse me.
I'll be right back. Sorry.

1062
01:02:25,062 --> 01:02:27,290
There, there, Manon.

1063
01:02:28,262 --> 01:02:29,860
Why are you crying?

1064
01:02:29,861 --> 01:02:33,700
- Me? Oh, it's the flowers. I'm, er... allergic.
- Oh! Oh, I'm so sorry.

1065
01:02:33,701 --> 01:02:35,661
- It's all right.
- Oh.

1066
01:02:35,662 --> 01:02:37,861
No, no, no, Manon.
It's fine, really.

1067
01:02:37,861 --> 01:02:43,165
- No, don't do that.
- Bloody things! I don't like them anyway.

1068
01:02:55,141 --> 01:02:57,019
- What would you do?
- Me?

1069
01:02:57,020 --> 01:03:01,258
Yes. You're clearly a woman of the
world. What do you think of him?

1070
01:03:01,259 --> 01:03:02,819
- Your husband?
- Yes.

1071
01:03:02,820 --> 01:03:07,258
- Well, I mean, he's fine. He's...
- Fine?

1072
01:03:07,259 --> 01:03:09,818
Actually, I think
he's a bit callous.

1073
01:03:09,819 --> 01:03:13,178
I'm sorry, I think
you could do better.

1074
01:03:13,179 --> 01:03:14,898
I think he probably...

1075
01:03:14,899 --> 01:03:18,297
I think he probably treats you
like a piece of jewellery.

1076
01:03:18,298 --> 01:03:19,898
I think he probably
treats you badly.

1077
01:03:19,899 --> 01:03:23,737
That's not to say he can't change.
I mean, they can change. People do change.

1078
01:03:23,738 --> 01:03:29,016
But it's easy to say I love you while
you're rolling around on expensive sheets.

1079
01:03:29,017 --> 01:03:32,728
It's so much harder
when they need washing.

1080
01:03:35,418 --> 01:03:40,336
Look, I'm not who you think I am. I'm
sorry, I'm not Miriam from Weymouth.

1081
01:03:40,337 --> 01:03:43,736
I'm not even Katie from Texas.
I'm just Kate from Surrey.

1082
01:03:43,737 --> 01:03:46,416
And my ex-husband is lying on the
floor next to your bed, I'm afraid.

1083
01:03:46,417 --> 01:03:48,175
- He is?
- Yep.

1084
01:03:48,176 --> 01:03:50,960
Oh! Hello.

1085
01:03:51,376 --> 01:03:53,895
- Hi.
- And why are you crying?

1086
01:03:53,896 --> 01:03:56,417
The cats. But don't throw
them out the window.

1087
01:03:56,417 --> 01:04:02,015
- Oh, he's really handsome.
- I know. It's irritating.

1088
01:04:02,016 --> 01:04:04,615
- Not sure about the moustache.
- I agree.

1089
01:04:04,616 --> 01:04:07,375
The thing is, you see, your
husband stole something from us

1090
01:04:07,376 --> 01:04:09,015
and from a lot of other
very good people.

1091
01:04:09,016 --> 01:04:12,174
Something very valuable
to us: our future.

1092
01:04:12,175 --> 01:04:18,535
And so we came here tonight to take
back what we feel is rightfully ours.

1093
01:04:18,536 --> 01:04:20,454
Oh. The diamond.

1094
01:04:20,455 --> 01:04:23,814
- It's not very imaginative, I grant you.
- Sorry, my back was killing me.

1095
01:04:25,055 --> 01:04:29,574
- Manon, open up. It's Vincent.
- Take it. I don't like it anyway.

1096
01:04:29,575 --> 01:04:32,326
Great. Here's the fake.

1097
01:04:34,415 --> 01:04:35,813
Manon!

1098
01:04:37,295 --> 01:04:38,998
What?

1099
01:04:42,974 --> 01:04:44,852
Why are you throwing
flowers out the window?

1100
01:04:44,853 --> 01:04:48,881
I'm allergic. Don't you
know anything about me?

1101
01:04:50,734 --> 01:04:55,362
You must take good care of this.
It's not a toy, it's very valuable.

1102
01:04:55,733 --> 01:04:57,853
More valuable than me?

1103
01:04:57,853 --> 01:05:03,771
Darling, there is nothing on earth that is
more valuable to me than me... than you!

1104
01:05:03,772 --> 01:05:06,076
You should know that.

1105
01:05:09,933 --> 01:05:14,484
And will you still love me even
when we are washing the sheets?

1106
01:05:21,771 --> 01:05:23,595
Ssh!

1107
01:05:27,052 --> 01:05:28,250
What are you doing?

1108
01:05:28,251 --> 01:05:30,090
I don't know. I thought
you were about to sneeze.

1109
01:05:30,091 --> 01:05:33,203
- Causing a distraction's supposed to stop it.
- That's hiccups.

1110
01:05:33,372 --> 01:05:35,719
Ah... yes.

1111
01:05:36,651 --> 01:05:39,163
I might sneeze again.

1112
01:05:44,250 --> 01:05:46,449
What are we doing?
We've got to get out of here.

1113
01:05:46,450 --> 01:05:48,290
Oh, OK.

1114
01:05:48,291 --> 01:05:50,474
- What, back the way we came?
- Yes!

1115
01:06:08,409 --> 01:06:12,329
- Oh! Sorry, old partner.
- Sorry, sorry.

1116
01:06:12,330 --> 01:06:13,792
Yeah, howdy.

1117
01:06:19,689 --> 01:06:24,327
Although not on the official schedule, my
new wife would like to say a few words.

1118
01:06:26,729 --> 01:06:32,608
A wise woman once told me that
you can love your husband

1119
01:06:32,609 --> 01:06:34,808
but you must also like him.

1120
01:06:38,127 --> 01:06:40,287
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1121
01:06:40,288 --> 01:06:44,240
And I finally realised that...

1122
01:06:45,487 --> 01:06:50,716
I don't love Vincent
or even like him.

1123
01:06:52,888 --> 01:06:56,359
So Vincent, darling...

1124
01:06:57,567 --> 01:06:59,599
I want a divorce.

1125
01:07:09,526 --> 01:07:14,438
Stop! Stop! There's been
a travesty of justice.

1126
01:07:16,165 --> 01:07:18,044
Catch them!

1127
01:07:18,045 --> 01:07:19,356
Catch them!

1128
01:07:20,885 --> 01:07:24,269
Hey! <i>Vive la révolution!</i>

1129
01:07:24,525 --> 01:07:26,795
<i>Vive la révolution!</i>

1130
01:07:27,405 --> 01:07:29,109
Oh!

1131
01:07:30,484 --> 01:07:33,476
- Oh, my God, no!
- No, no.

1132
01:07:42,565 --> 01:07:44,628
- Sorry, sorry.
- Sorry.

1133
01:07:44,923 --> 01:07:46,323
Ooh! Ow!

1134
01:07:46,324 --> 01:07:49,707
I knew there was something
familiar about you.

1135
01:07:49,723 --> 01:07:51,522
Ooh!

1136
01:07:51,524 --> 01:07:52,803
Ow!

1137
01:07:52,804 --> 01:07:54,508
Oh, no! They're real.

1138
01:07:54,883 --> 01:08:00,281
OK, let's make this simple.
Where is the real diamond?

1139
01:08:02,483 --> 01:08:04,922
Bloody hell.

1140
01:08:11,763 --> 01:08:14,362
- Oh!
- Oh, that's a whole other level of pain.

1141
01:08:14,363 --> 01:08:19,122
Look, we're just a disgruntled employee and
his pushy wife who want back what's theirs.

1142
01:08:19,123 --> 01:08:21,161
- You didn't say ex-wife.
- No, I didn't, did I?

1143
01:08:21,162 --> 01:08:22,961
- Mmm...
- We should focus.

1144
01:08:22,962 --> 01:08:25,506
- Right.
- Have you ever heard of karma?

1145
01:08:26,161 --> 01:08:29,080
Perhaps you're being punished
for all the bad things

1146
01:08:29,081 --> 01:08:32,104
that you might have
done in your life.

1147
01:08:34,721 --> 01:08:36,664
It's just a thought.

1148
01:08:37,482 --> 01:08:40,800
Oh, no! That's just mean!
You're just being a bully now!

1149
01:08:40,801 --> 01:08:43,029
Be grateful, I don't hit women.

1150
01:08:43,561 --> 01:08:47,709
Now, tell me where my diamond is!

1151
01:09:02,640 --> 01:09:04,911
I swallowed it.

1152
01:09:05,680 --> 01:09:07,678
I sold the diamond.

1153
01:09:07,679 --> 01:09:08,960
What?

1154
01:09:08,960 --> 01:09:11,908
I swapped it and sold the real one.

1155
01:09:12,678 --> 01:09:17,357
Gave the money to charity,
an orphanage in Calcutta.

1156
01:09:17,358 --> 01:09:18,958
What? Why?

1157
01:09:18,959 --> 01:09:21,558
A test, to see if you
really loved me.

1158
01:09:21,559 --> 01:09:24,358
You're crazy. I'll
deal with you later.

1159
01:09:24,358 --> 01:09:26,902
Get rid of them.

1160
01:09:27,239 --> 01:09:28,357
Oh, no.

1161
01:09:28,358 --> 01:09:30,757
OK, er...

1162
01:09:30,758 --> 01:09:33,237
If I'd known, I'd have
worn better underwear.

1163
01:09:33,238 --> 01:09:35,716
I don't think it's your underwear
you should be worrying about, Pen.

1164
01:09:35,717 --> 01:09:37,597
- These things reveal everything.
- What do you mean?

1165
01:09:37,598 --> 01:09:40,502
- Yeah, every nook and cranny.
- Oh, God!

1166
01:09:42,758 --> 01:09:44,625
What are you looking at?

1167
01:09:45,876 --> 01:09:48,704
Damn cheek!

1168
01:09:56,637 --> 01:09:58,436
Oh, yes, that's, er... Saigon,

1169
01:09:58,437 --> 01:10:01,796
Vietnam, 1964.

1170
01:10:01,797 --> 01:10:04,236
Took a bit of shrapnel, yeah.

1171
01:10:04,237 --> 01:10:07,828
Bloody hell, they left some forceps
in there. Look, the clamp's in there.

1172
01:10:08,236 --> 01:10:09,595
- I didn't know that.
- You can go.

1173
01:10:09,596 --> 01:10:11,060
Bloody Vietnam.

1174
01:10:12,396 --> 01:10:15,834
- Take them to the cliff.
- Huh? The cliff?

1175
01:10:15,835 --> 01:10:18,435
Whisky? A last drink?

1176
01:10:18,436 --> 01:10:20,835
Not my tipple.

1177
01:10:25,995 --> 01:10:28,994
- I do hope they'll be all right, Jerry.
- I'm sure they'll be fine, love.

1178
01:10:28,995 --> 01:10:30,700
- Do you think?
- Yeah.

1179
01:10:41,874 --> 01:10:44,393
Stop whistling, Richard.

1180
01:10:44,395 --> 01:10:47,393
- Please, stop whistling. It drives me mad.
- Helps me relax, Kate.

1181
01:10:47,394 --> 01:10:49,992
Well, it doesn't help me relax.
It's driving me bloody mad.

1182
01:10:49,993 --> 01:10:52,177
OK, I'll stop. I've stopped
whistling now, OK?

1183
01:11:06,552 --> 01:11:08,831
We've stopped.

1184
01:11:08,832 --> 01:11:10,580
Yes.

1185
01:11:16,593 --> 01:11:18,940
- We're moving.
- Yes.

1186
01:11:28,471 --> 01:11:30,431
- Kate.
- What?

1187
01:11:30,432 --> 01:11:32,350
- I just wanted to say...
- What?

1188
01:11:32,351 --> 01:11:34,471
I just wanted to say, Kate,
that whatever happens...

1189
01:11:34,472 --> 01:11:38,859
- You're not trying to do a final speech, are you?
- No, not at all. Well, maybe a little.

1190
01:11:42,272 --> 01:11:43,910
It's just that...

1191
01:11:43,911 --> 01:11:45,470
- Shut up!
- All right, I will.

1192
01:11:50,631 --> 01:11:52,094
Oh!

1193
01:11:52,670 --> 01:11:54,615
- Oh!
- Oh!

1194
01:11:56,990 --> 01:11:59,654
Don't... move.

1195
01:12:09,789 --> 01:12:11,988
- Oh.
- Ohh!

1196
01:12:11,990 --> 01:12:14,108
- What's going on?
- We're going back. We're going back!

1197
01:12:14,109 --> 01:12:16,709
- No, no, no, no, no.
- Ssh, ssh, ssh, ssh, ssh.

1198
01:12:16,709 --> 01:12:19,014
No, no, no, no.

1199
01:12:20,509 --> 01:12:22,627
I just wanted to say
I'm sorry, Kate.

1200
01:12:22,628 --> 01:12:23,947
What for?

1201
01:12:23,949 --> 01:12:26,581
For not being a good husband.

1202
01:12:27,788 --> 01:12:29,268
I'm sorry too, then.

1203
01:12:29,269 --> 01:12:31,228
For what?

1204
01:12:31,229 --> 01:12:32,907
For not letting you be one.

1205
01:12:32,908 --> 01:12:34,627
What do you mean?

1206
01:12:34,628 --> 01:12:36,386
- We were too young.
- Uh-huh.

1207
01:12:36,388 --> 01:12:40,853
It takes two, you know, to totally ruin
a marriage, and I played my part.

1208
01:12:41,029 --> 01:12:42,307
Oh, God!

1209
01:12:42,308 --> 01:12:44,826
Anyway, what does it
matter now? We're...

1210
01:12:47,107 --> 01:12:48,571
We're going to die!

1211
01:12:51,427 --> 01:12:55,816
- Richard!
- It's OK. I've got you. Hold on.

1212
01:12:57,227 --> 01:13:00,218
Kate, I think we should try again.

1213
01:13:01,308 --> 01:13:03,826
- Try what again?
- Me and you.

1214
01:13:03,827 --> 01:13:05,826
What are you talking
about, Richard?

1215
01:13:05,827 --> 01:13:08,265
I think we should finally sail round the
world, like we've always talked about.

1216
01:13:08,266 --> 01:13:10,306
I've had such a great
time these past few days.

1217
01:13:10,307 --> 01:13:13,747
Could you just concentrate?
Concentrate on holding on!

1218
01:13:13,747 --> 01:13:16,585
- Well, don't you feel anything, Kate?
- Yes, fear!

1219
01:13:16,586 --> 01:13:18,933
All right. OK.
Well, just think about it.

1220
01:13:20,505 --> 01:13:23,705
I like you, I really like you.

1221
01:13:29,145 --> 01:13:31,208
Come on, you fucker!

1222
01:13:32,225 --> 01:13:33,973
Come on!

1223
01:13:43,744 --> 01:13:45,024
- Are you OK?
- Manon!

1224
01:13:45,025 --> 01:13:48,864
- Manon!
- Oh! Oh, thank you. Thank you!

1225
01:13:48,864 --> 01:13:52,623
Oh, no, it is I who should be thanking
you for making me see things clearly.

1226
01:13:52,624 --> 01:13:53,983
<i>Merci beaucoup.</i>

1227
01:13:55,585 --> 01:13:57,812
We must go. Help me.

1228
01:13:58,384 --> 01:14:00,263
Here we go.

1229
01:14:15,903 --> 01:14:18,902
- Nice girl, passionate.
- Oh, I do hope she'll be all right.

1230
01:14:18,902 --> 01:14:21,370
Oh, a headstrong girl
like her, she'll be fine.

1231
01:14:21,623 --> 01:14:23,222
We're gonna have to swim
out of here. You know that?

1232
01:14:23,223 --> 01:14:26,581
- We'll be sitting ducks.
- Yeah, well, do you have a better idea?

1233
01:14:26,583 --> 01:14:28,021
I know a man with a boat.

1234
01:14:28,022 --> 01:14:29,290
- You do?
- Yeah.

1235
01:14:35,541 --> 01:14:38,621
- Online?
- Yes, Richard, online.

1236
01:14:38,621 --> 01:14:43,860
You chat, you get to know each other, and you
agree to meet up, if you like each other.

1237
01:14:43,861 --> 01:14:46,059
- But you've never met him?
- No, not yet.

1238
01:14:46,060 --> 01:14:47,700
So you don't even know
if you'll like him.

1239
01:14:47,701 --> 01:14:49,341
Well, he's 57. He lives in Paris

1240
01:14:49,341 --> 01:14:51,660
and has house and a boat in the
south of France. What's not to like?

1241
01:14:51,661 --> 01:14:54,849
Good heavens, Kate!
How shallow you've become.

1242
01:14:57,861 --> 01:15:00,372
That must be the captain.

1243
01:15:02,501 --> 01:15:06,606
Bonjour, Kate.
It's me, Jean-Baptiste.

1244
01:15:07,340 --> 01:15:09,371
Bloody hell!

1245
01:15:17,779 --> 01:15:19,899
You know, I'm twice your age.

1246
01:15:19,900 --> 01:15:22,858
What can I say? I like older women.

1247
01:15:22,859 --> 01:15:25,218
Why lie on your profile?

1248
01:15:25,218 --> 01:15:30,058
I want women to see me as a mature man.
Otherwise, I feel like a total cliché, you know?

1249
01:15:30,059 --> 01:15:35,692
Young, rich, handsome, with a
speedboat... So terribly predictable.

1250
01:15:38,218 --> 01:15:40,337
He's your lover?

1251
01:15:40,339 --> 01:15:42,138
Ex-lover.

1252
01:15:42,139 --> 01:15:44,409
But you still have
some feelings for him?

1253
01:15:49,217 --> 01:15:51,010
I don't know.

1254
01:15:51,378 --> 01:15:53,802
It's not good to look back.

1255
01:15:54,578 --> 01:15:56,136
No, you're right.

1256
01:15:56,137 --> 01:15:58,649
- It can make you feel a bit sick.
- Oh.

1257
01:16:03,217 --> 01:16:04,815
Shall we head back?

1258
01:16:04,816 --> 01:16:07,337
- Well, actually...
- We are going out.

1259
01:16:07,337 --> 01:16:10,056
- Oh, really? Out?
- Yes, on a date.

1260
01:16:10,057 --> 01:16:12,655
- Well, not a date. Not...
- Yes, a date.

1261
01:16:12,656 --> 01:16:15,054
But what about the, er...

1262
01:16:15,055 --> 01:16:16,616
...diamond?

1263
01:16:16,617 --> 01:16:18,768
You can handle that, can't you?

1264
01:16:19,576 --> 01:16:22,256
Are you telling me you don't
want to see this through now?

1265
01:16:22,256 --> 01:16:26,454
No, I... Well, I think so. I mean,
can't you deal with it on your own?

1266
01:16:26,455 --> 01:16:28,563
I'll meet you at the
rendezvous in Paris.

1267
01:16:29,656 --> 01:16:31,095
Right.

1268
01:16:31,097 --> 01:16:33,574
Right, I see. Well...

1269
01:16:33,575 --> 01:16:37,454
I suppose I did start all this for a
reason and the reason was for the...

1270
01:16:37,455 --> 01:16:40,119
for the people, for...
for Doreen, for...

1271
01:16:42,375 --> 01:16:44,893
Right, I'll be off, then.

1272
01:16:44,894 --> 01:16:47,885
- You take good care of her.
- I will.

1273
01:16:54,614 --> 01:16:58,934
So, first of all, we have
some champagne at my villa.

1274
01:16:58,935 --> 01:17:02,013
OK. It's a bit early,
isn't it, for champagne?

1275
01:17:02,014 --> 01:17:05,246
It's never too early for champagne.
It's always too late.

1276
01:17:07,694 --> 01:17:09,213
Ah!

1277
01:17:09,214 --> 01:17:11,852
Oh, thank goodness. You made it.

1278
01:17:11,853 --> 01:17:13,052
Where's Kate?

1279
01:17:13,053 --> 01:17:15,531
Ah, she's not here.

1280
01:17:15,532 --> 01:17:17,237
Where is she?

1281
01:17:17,732 --> 01:17:19,372
- She's with a Frenchman.
- Oh!

1282
01:17:19,372 --> 01:17:22,653
- What Frenchman?
- Jean-Baptiste.

1283
01:17:22,654 --> 01:17:24,292
You knew about him?

1284
01:17:24,293 --> 01:17:26,572
Oh! Oh, right. Jean-Baptiste, yeah.

1285
01:17:26,573 --> 01:17:28,812
Did everybody know about the
Frenchman apart from me?

1286
01:17:28,813 --> 01:17:31,292
But why is she meeting him?
You're back together now.

1287
01:17:31,293 --> 01:17:33,572
No, Pen, we're not back together.

1288
01:17:33,573 --> 01:17:36,291
You seemed so happy so we
just went along with it.

1289
01:17:36,292 --> 01:17:38,531
I suppose it was a bit
of a long shot anyway.

1290
01:17:38,532 --> 01:17:41,730
Probably wouldn't have
worked second time around.

1291
01:17:41,731 --> 01:17:43,731
Exactly.

1292
01:17:43,732 --> 01:17:47,250
Anyway, the diamond. Where is it?

1293
01:17:47,251 --> 01:17:49,531
- Ah, yeah.
- There's been a slight delay.

1294
01:17:49,531 --> 01:17:52,883
Yeah, but... Pen's got me
on the old prune juice.

1295
01:17:53,531 --> 01:17:55,090
Should get the bomb doors open.

1296
01:17:57,051 --> 01:17:59,250
Maybe? No, false alarm.

1297
01:18:23,810 --> 01:18:26,689
- Where are you going?
- Ah, good morning.

1298
01:18:26,690 --> 01:18:28,481
There is a robe on the chair.

1299
01:18:34,610 --> 01:18:38,488
- I'm so sorry about last night.
- Oh, Jean-Baptiste, it was lovely.

1300
01:18:38,489 --> 01:18:41,993
- Yeah, but I drunk too much and...
- It happens. You're young.

1301
01:18:42,208 --> 01:18:45,128
You've got much more experience
than me. That thing that you did...

1302
01:18:45,128 --> 01:18:47,368
Oh, thank you.

1303
01:18:47,369 --> 01:18:49,288
So, what would you
like to do today?

1304
01:18:49,289 --> 01:18:51,447
We can have some
breakfast outside or...

1305
01:18:51,448 --> 01:18:54,286
We can take my boat somewhere.
You can practise your French.

1306
01:18:55,927 --> 01:18:57,555
Ooh.

1307
01:18:58,048 --> 01:19:00,206
- You like this song?
- I love this song.

1308
01:19:00,207 --> 01:19:02,926
- Who is it?
- Free. You know...

1309
01:19:02,927 --> 01:19:05,206
♪ All right now ♪

1310
01:19:05,207 --> 01:19:07,316
No, I don't know this band.

1311
01:19:07,767 --> 01:19:11,151
No... of course you don't.

1312
01:19:14,846 --> 01:19:18,926
It was the linseeds that ultimately
did it, such a smooth transition.

1313
01:19:18,927 --> 01:19:20,405
- Well done, Jerry.
- Darling.

1314
01:19:20,406 --> 01:19:23,606
Amazing. Look at it.
It's beautiful. Touch it.

1315
01:19:23,606 --> 01:19:25,671
No, I think I'll pass, Jerry.

1316
01:19:26,046 --> 01:19:27,604
Thank you.

1317
01:19:27,605 --> 01:19:30,924
Where is this man, Diamond Dave?

1318
01:19:30,925 --> 01:19:33,350
Patience, my dear, patience.

1319
01:19:34,205 --> 01:19:36,124
- I'm sure she's coming, Richard.
- Mmm.

1320
01:19:36,125 --> 01:19:38,277
I don't think so, Pen.

1321
01:19:39,205 --> 01:19:40,877
Thanks, anyway.

1322
01:19:41,484 --> 01:19:45,364
I don't understand. What
is the Eye of the Rainbow?

1323
01:19:45,365 --> 01:19:48,083
It's a diamond that we stole.

1324
01:19:48,084 --> 01:19:53,403
But first we had to kidnap the Texans, scuba
to the chateau and break into a wedding.

1325
01:19:53,405 --> 01:19:56,233
- You stole a diamond?
- Yes.

1326
01:19:57,804 --> 01:20:00,483
- I'm not gonna make it.
- Yes, you will.

1327
01:20:09,965 --> 01:20:13,882
It's Diamond Dave.
He hasn't changed a bit.

1328
01:20:13,883 --> 01:20:17,071
- Don't take less than ten.
- Right you are.

1329
01:20:27,562 --> 01:20:30,321
- I just don't get it.
- What, my love?

1330
01:20:30,322 --> 01:20:32,442
How you know all these people?

1331
01:20:32,443 --> 01:20:34,921
- Who?
- Well, Diamond bloody Dave.

1332
01:20:34,923 --> 01:20:37,642
- Oh, you know, way back.
- No, I don't know, Jerry.

1333
01:20:37,643 --> 01:20:41,081
I don't know about Saigon or
Guam or the Foreign Legion.

1334
01:20:41,082 --> 01:20:44,600
- Or even Diamond bloody Dave. I really don't.
- It's all right. Calm down.

1335
01:20:44,601 --> 01:20:47,560
No, I won't calm down.
Who are these people, Jerry?

1336
01:20:47,561 --> 01:20:52,000
These contacts? All that metal
in your body? This past life?

1337
01:20:52,001 --> 01:20:54,400
I thought I knew you.
I thought we were the same.

1338
01:20:54,400 --> 01:20:56,792
Oh, Pen.

1339
01:21:00,001 --> 01:21:02,545
I'm more than the sum of my parts.

1340
01:21:02,961 --> 01:21:07,392
- What does that mean?
- I've got no idea.

1341
01:21:07,760 --> 01:21:11,559
But what I do know
is that I love you.

1342
01:21:11,560 --> 01:21:16,428
Always have, always will. OK?

1343
01:21:17,160 --> 01:21:19,919
- OK.
- Yeah!

1344
01:21:19,920 --> 01:21:23,151
- Got 15.
- Bloody hell.

1345
01:21:33,759 --> 01:21:36,118
You can literally go anywhere
from here, can't you?

1346
01:21:36,119 --> 01:21:38,870
Well, we've got a
briefcase full of cash.

1347
01:21:39,799 --> 01:21:41,437
Penelope!

1348
01:21:41,438 --> 01:21:43,786
There's one back to
London in 50 minutes.

1349
01:21:45,639 --> 01:21:48,598
No, I don't think we
should get that one.

1350
01:21:48,599 --> 01:21:50,705
- Kate!
- Hey-hey!

1351
01:21:52,877 --> 01:21:54,957
Listen, what do you think about...

1352
01:21:54,958 --> 01:21:58,582
I don't know, maybe doing a bit of
travelling before we head home?

1353
01:21:59,557 --> 01:22:00,749
Travelling?

1354
01:22:02,197 --> 01:22:05,396
- Well...
- Stupid idea, right?

1355
01:22:05,397 --> 01:22:07,189
Yes.

1356
01:22:07,758 --> 01:22:13,029
A crazy... daft... stupid...

1357
01:22:13,797 --> 01:22:16,116
but brilliant idea.

1358
01:22:16,117 --> 01:22:17,715
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Why the hell not?

1359
01:22:17,716 --> 01:22:20,475
- What have we got to lose?
- Apart from our dignity?

1360
01:22:20,477 --> 01:22:22,748
Either way, it's
worth investigating.

1361
01:22:22,876 --> 01:22:26,021
Definitely. Let's investigate.

1362
01:22:27,036 --> 01:22:29,314
Would you see that the
relevant people get this?

1363
01:22:29,315 --> 01:22:30,516
It would be an honour, my friend.

1364
01:22:30,517 --> 01:22:33,595
I've, er... taken a bit out. You can
stash the rest under the mattress.

1365
01:22:33,596 --> 01:22:36,915
Don't worry, old pal. We've got a
safe house built under the stairs.

1366
01:22:36,916 --> 01:22:39,580
- We do?
- Yeah.

1367
01:22:41,196 --> 01:22:43,304
<i>Bon voyage</i>, my old friends.

1368
01:22:43,875 --> 01:22:45,754
- I'll feed the cat.
- Oh, thank you.

1369
01:22:45,755 --> 01:22:47,195
- Look after yourselves.
- We will.

1370
01:22:47,196 --> 01:22:48,354
Thank you.

1371
01:22:48,355 --> 01:22:50,875
- Come along, Jerry.
- Be very, very naughty.

1372
01:22:50,875 --> 01:22:53,659
- It's is very heavy, Jerry.
- Hey-hey!

1373
01:22:54,194 --> 01:22:56,619
- Come on, my love.
- I say...

1374
01:22:57,675 --> 01:22:59,619
Oh... yes.

1375
01:23:00,634 --> 01:23:02,426
<i>Merci.</i>

1376
01:23:04,794 --> 01:23:06,552
Come on.

1377
01:23:06,554 --> 01:23:08,182
Come on!

1378
01:23:19,633 --> 01:23:21,392
Oh, yay!

1379
01:23:21,393 --> 01:23:22,912
Right. Yay!

1380
01:23:22,913 --> 01:23:24,586
Hey-hey-hey!

1381
